# Push scope notes:
# - D:/v5 tracks source, docs, configs, Vivado-owned files, and fixed offline
#   build inputs by default.
# - Cache, temporary files, reproducible publish outputs, generated build/run
#   outputs, non-input compressed packages, and test proof/evidence captures
#   are excluded by .gitignore and by the desktop push script before commit.

# Unified-diff context lines and format-patch signatures intentionally carry
# trailing spaces, so the generic staged whitespace checker must not reject
# canonical Yocto patch inputs for their patch syntax.
*.patch -whitespace

board/third_party/petalinux-source-packages/** filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
board/third_party/petalinux-source-packages/v5_source_packages.json -filter -merge text diff
